<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n33180a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n33" href="#n33180a">N33 (VI.B.4)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n33all.htm#n33180a"> 180(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Anubis v / Am. mit ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[In the Judgement Scene of the Papyrus of Ani]</font> the heart of the deceased is being weighed against the feather of Ma&acirc;t by <mark>Anubis</mark>, who scrutinizes the tongue of the balance with great care; close to the pillar of the scales is the monster <mark>&Acirc;m-mit</mark>, who is ready to devour the heart in the event of its being found light. <small> E.A. Wallis Budge, <a name="BOD1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BOD1"><cite title="source">The Book of the Dead</cite></a>, 2nd ed. (1909) lxxxvi</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
